## Grafana Dashboard Model

The visualization of Netflix movie performance analytics was built using a dynamic Grafana dashboard.  
The dashboard integrates with the dataset stored in **Google BigQuery** under the schema:

> **Schema Name:** `netflix_analysis_2010_2025_public`

The Grafana dashboard JSON model was exported for replication and reference purposes.

> **Grafana Model File:** `netflix_dashboard_model.json`

### Description:
- The dashboard visualizes key metrics such as:
  - Total number of movies analyzed
  - ROI trends over time
  - Genre-wise performance distribution
  - Country-wise ROI leaders
  - Popularity vs ROI relationships
  - Hidden gems with high ROI but lower popularity
- Each panel was customized to allow dynamic filtering and drill-down for better user interactivity.

### Access Instructions:
- Import the `netflix_dashboard_model.json` file into Grafana.
- Configure the data source to point to the BigQuery project and dataset (`netflix_analysis_2010_2025_public`).
- The dashboard will render automatically with all predefined panels and visualizations.

---


# **Schema**

| Column Name | Data Type | Description |
|:------------|:----------|:------------|
| title | STRING | Movie title |
| genres | STRING | Associated movie genres |
| production_countries | STRING | Country where movie was produced |
| original_language | STRING | Original language code |
| release_year | INTEGER | Year of release |
| vote_count | INTEGER | Audience votes received |
| popularity | FLOAT | Popularity index score |
| budget | FLOAT | Production cost in USD |
| revenue | FLOAT | Total revenue generated |
| roi | FLOAT | Return on Investment (revenue/budget) |
| profit | FLOAT | Profit earned (revenue - budget) |
| efficiency | FLOAT | ROI scaled relative to budget |

